# Two ways to supply these values, both self-loaded by Program.cs at startup
# so any MCP client (Claude Code, Codex CLI, pi, ...) that just runs
# `dotnet run --project <this folder>` picks them up automatically without
# needing to carry secrets itself:
#
#   1. Copy this file to .env in this same directory (gitignored) and fill
#      in real values, OR
#   2. Use .NET User Secrets, e.g.:
#        dotnet user-secrets set AUTH0_CLIENT_ID "..."
#        dotnet user-secrets set AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET "..."
#
# A real environment variable, if already set, always wins over both.
HARMONY_MCP_URL=https://harmony-resolver.duckdns.org/mcp
AUTH0_DOMAIN=dev-bozmund.eu.auth0.com
AUTH0_CLIENT_ID=replace-me
AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET=replace-me
AUTH0_AUDIENCE=https://harmony-resolver-diagnostics
